- Proceeds payable to a named beneficiary (someone other than 'estate') are paid directly to the beneficiary and do not flow through the estate. This means that no probate or executor fees will be deducted from, and no estate creditors can make claims against, these proceeds;
- Proceeds are available to the beneficiary as soon as the claim is approved since they do not become part of the estate. Settlement of
